  "contenu": [
    {
      "type": "texte",
      "value": "Soit la fonction $V \\colon \\R^2 \\to \\R$ définie par $$V(r,\\theta) = \\dfrac{\\cos \\theta}{r^2}$$"
    },
    {
      "type": "question",
      "value": "Donner l'ensemble de définition de $V$."
    },
    {
      "type": "reponse",
      "value": "$\\mathcal{D}_V = \\R^* \\times \\R$"
    },
    {
      "type": "question",
      "value": "Calculer les dérivées partielles $\\dpa{V}{r}$ et $\\dpa{V}{\\theta}$."
    },
    {
      "type": "reponse",
      "value": "pour $(r,\\theta) \\in \\mathcal{D}_V$, on a \n\t\t\t\\[ \\dpa{V}{r} = -\\frac{2}{r^3}\\cos\\theta, \\ \\ \\dpa{V}{\\theta} = -\\frac{1}{r^2}\\sin\\theta \\]"
    },
    {
      "type": "question",
      "value": "Calculer les dérivées partielles secondes $\\dpsp{V}{r}$, $\\dpa{V}{\\theta}$ et $\\dpsm{V}{r}{\\theta}$."
    },
    {
      "type": "reponse",
      "value": "pour $(r,\\theta) \\in \\mathcal{D}_V$, on a\n\t\t\t$$\\begin{align*} \n\t\t\t\\dpsp{V}{r} &= \\dpa{}{r}\\left[ -\\frac{2}{r^3}\\cos\\theta \\right] = \\frac{6}{r^4}\\cos\\theta \\\\\n\t\t\t\\dpsp{V}{\\theta} &= \\dpa{}{\\theta}\\left[ -\\frac{1}{r^2}\\sin\\theta \\right] = -\\frac{1}{r^2}\\cos\\theta \\\\\n\t\t\t\\dpsm{V}{r}{\\theta} &= \\dpa{}{r}\\left[ -\\frac{1}{r^2}\\sin\\theta \\right] = \\frac{2}{r^3}\\sin\\theta\n\t\t\t\\end{align*}$$"
    },
    {
      "type": "question",
      "value": "En déduire que $$\\sin \\theta \\ \\dpa{}{r} \\left[ r^2 \\dpa{V}{r} \\right]  + \\dpa{}{\\theta} \\left[ \\sin \\theta \\dpa{V}{\\theta} \\right]  = 0.$$"
    },
    {
      "type": "reponse",
      "value": "On a\n\t\t\t\\begin{eqnarray*}\n\t\t\t\t\\lefteqn{\\sin \\theta \\ \\dpa{}{r} \\left[ r^2 \\dpa{V}{r} \\right]  + \\dpa{}{\\theta} \\left[ \\sin \\theta \\dpa{V}{\\theta} \\right]} \\\\\n\t\t\t\t&=& \\sin\\theta \\left[ 2r \\dpa{V}{r} + r^2 \\dpsp{V}{r} \\right] + \\left[ \\cos\\theta \\dpa{V}{\\theta} + \\sin\\theta \\dpsp{V}{\\theta} \\right] \\\\\n\t\t\t\t&=& \\sin\\theta \\left[ 2r (-\\frac{2}{r^3}\\cos\\theta) + r^2 \\frac{6}{r^4}\\cos\\theta \\right] + \\left[ \\cos\\theta (-\\frac{1}{r^2}\\sin\\theta) + \\sin\\theta (-\\frac{1}{r^2}\\cos\\theta) \\right] \\\\\n\t\t\t\t&=& \\frac{\\cos\\theta\\sin\\theta}{r^2}(-4+ 6-1-1) \\\\\n\t\t\t\t&=& 0\n\t\t\\end{eqnarray*}"
    }
  ]
}